Sentencas: A series of planar billets of NiO/Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 (NiO/GDC) anodes for solid oxide fuel cells are fabricated by the method of microdrop 3D printing using a pneumatic dispenser.
Titulo: Electrical Properties and Microstructure of 3D Printed Anodes Based on the Ni/Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Composite for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The porosity and the coefficient of sintering-induced shrinkage of anode billets are studied as a function of their preparation method.
Titulo: Electrical Properties and Microstructure of 3D Printed Anodes Based on the Ni/Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Composite for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The anode billets are reduced to obtain Ni/Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 cermet and the thus obtained samples are studied as regards the effect of printing parameters on their morphology and structure.
Titulo: Electrical Properties and Microstructure of 3D Printed Anodes Based on the Ni/Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Composite for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It is shown that the use of 3D printing increases the porosity of the Ni/GDC composite from 7 to 23% as compared with the casted samples, on retention of the high conductivity of (2.82 +/- 0.06) x 10(3) S/cm.
Titulo: Electrical Properties and Microstructure of 3D Printed Anodes Based on the Ni/Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 Composite for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
